<br>
Around 8k damage (2x mana pool size) is the approximate damage most MB wizards can push out on a consistent basis. If you're lucky, a crit, and double that figure. Very hard/near impossible to resist and fast, but not as mana efficient as using regular spells.<br>
<br>
See, problem is, with Frenzied as it is right now, BO5 almost matches that, somewhat (at least in haste value), and overall damage with Pet + Muzzle + BO4 is approximately the same as FB. Since that's the case, exactally what's the point of it? VI screwed it up when they downgraded FB's stats from what it was BEFORE to what it is now.<br>
<br>
Frankly, 36 seconds of uber arsekicking pet and a sizable explosion at the end would be fine, IF the pet really seriously and truely kicked the living daylights out of the mob it was on. The Petlessness afterwards is equivilent to a wizard being OOM (defenseless), and as easily corrected (cast new pet) as a wizard's 'punishment' is for the skill (Trod/Epic). <br>
<br>
Kill any xps mob in 36 seconds (perhaps multiples), or punch down some serious hurt on a raid mob. FB needs to work as a real serious damage increase to the pet first. It fails to do that even as it stands now.<br>
<br>
Flurries need to be verified as working first. Rampage, does it improve damage any? AoE broke like a joke. Does the +200 attack on it improve the pet's &quot;to hit&quot; on high end (60+) mobs? <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
